schema_text:
DATABASE SCHEMA ANALYSIS
==================================================

TABLE: departments
Rows: 25
Columns:
  • dept_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • name (TEXT) [NOT NULL] (samples: Dept 1, Dept 2, Dept 3)
  • location (TEXT) (samples: Remote, CA, NY)
  • budget (REAL) (samples: 645522.23, 1447643.66, 783735.85)
  • created_at (TEXT) (samples: 2025-08-09T17:03:32.)

TABLE: employees
Rows: 10,000
Columns:
  • emp_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • dept_id (INTEGER) [FK → departments.dept_id] (samples: 22, 4, 18)
  • emp_uuid (TEXT) (samples: d9b3f421-31bf-43b4-8, 25694e57-0433-4ca6-b, cb61f73f-83ef-4cf5-a)
  • first_name (TEXT) (samples: Linda, Christopher, Timothy)
  • last_name (TEXT) (samples: Brown, Haynes, Powell)
  • email (TEXT) (samples: linda.brown.738798@e, christopher.haynes.8, timothy.powell.38816)
  • hire_date (TEXT) (samples: 2022-01-17, 2019-09-17, 2015-05-03)
  • role (TEXT) (samples: Engineer, QA, Senior Engineer)
  • salary (REAL) (samples: 28236.114016923002, 25000.0, 30450.09122566627)
  • manager_id (INTEGER) [FK → employees.emp_id] (samples: 2647, 2525, 5663)
  • profile_json (TEXT) (samples: {"bio": "Seem buildi, {"bio": "Smile late , {"bio": "Community b)
  • active (INTEGER) (samples: 1)
  • created_at (TEXT) (samples: 2025-08-09T17:03:32.)
  • updated_at (TEXT) (samples: 2025-08-09T17:03:32.)
Relationships:
  • manager_id → employees.emp_id
  • dept_id → departments.dept_id

TABLE: projects
Rows: 1,000
Columns:
  • proj_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • dept_id (INTEGER) [FK → departments.dept_id] (samples: 19, 23, 8)
  • name (TEXT) (samples: Project Avoid 1, Project Catch 2, Project Political 3)
  • description (TEXT) (samples: Case compare number , Democratic thus supp, Collection wife cour)
  • start_date (TEXT) (samples: 2021-05-04, 2023-02-20, 2023-06-12)
  • end_date (TEXT) (samples: 2022-05-26T00:00:00, 2024-12-03T00:00:00, 2025-12-25T00:00:00)
  • status (TEXT) (samples: completed, planned)
  • budget (REAL) (samples: 132150.53, 169450.05, 140261.89)
  • config_json (TEXT) (samples: {"stack": ["rust", ", {"stack": ["python",, {"stack": ["rust", ")
  • created_at (TEXT) (samples: 2025-08-09T17:03:34.)
Relationships:
  • dept_id → departments.dept_id

TABLE: tasks
Rows: 12,339
Columns:
  • task_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • proj_id (INTEGER) [FK → projects.proj_id] (samples: 1)
  • assigned_to (INTEGER) [FK → employees.emp_id] (samples: 9672, 8574, 7613)
  • title (TEXT) (samples: Sort financial look , Great least debate d, Vote whether wear dr)
  • description (TEXT) (samples: Common admit if sour, Item myself student , Beat marriage have p)
  • status (TEXT) (samples: Done, In Progress)
  • priority (INTEGER) (samples: 1, 4, 5)
  • due_date (TEXT) (samples: 2026-03-17, 2026-06-03, 2026-03-13)
  • created_at (TEXT) (samples: 2025-08-09T17:03:34.)
Relationships:
  • assigned_to → employees.emp_id
  • proj_id → projects.proj_id

TABLE: clients
Rows: 500
Columns:
  • client_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • name (TEXT) (samples: Sparks, Harrison and, Moore PLC, Watkins-Cisneros)
  • industry (TEXT) (samples: Manufacturing, Tech, Retail)
  • contact_email (TEXT) (samples: williamsmaria@eaton-, ashleybaker@bryant.b, dthompson@cortez.com)
  • created_at (TEXT) (samples: 2025-08-09T17:03:34.)

TABLE: contracts
Rows: 1,000
Columns:
  • contract_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • client_id (INTEGER) [FK → clients.client_id] (samples: 309, 45, 121)
  • proj_id (INTEGER) [FK → projects.proj_id] (samples: 299, 182, 663)
  • amount (REAL) (samples: 1079983.93, 654977.53, 1093101.62)
  • signed_date (TEXT) (samples: 2024-03-31, 2024-02-24, 2024-06-13)
  • terms_json (TEXT) (samples: {"duration_months": , {"duration_months": , {"duration_months": )
  • created_at (TEXT) (samples: 2025-08-09T17:03:34.)
Relationships:
  • proj_id → projects.proj_id
  • client_id → clients.client_id

TABLE: skills
Rows: 60
Columns:
  • skill_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • name (TEXT) (samples: Python, SQL, Java)

TABLE: employee_skills
Rows: 34,675
Columns:
  • emp_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] [FK → employees.emp_id] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • skill_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] [FK → skills.skill_id] (samples: 36, 34, 42)
  • level (INTEGER) (samples: 1, 2, 5)
Relationships:
  • skill_id → skills.skill_id
  • emp_id → employees.emp_id

TABLE: emp_projects
Rows: 19,972
Columns:
  • emp_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] [FK → employees.emp_id] (samples: 585, 5053, 4938)
  • proj_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] [FK → projects.proj_id] (samples: 845, 406, 880)
  • assigned_at (TEXT) (samples: 2025-05-24, 2024-04-29, 2022-12-24)
  • role_on_project (TEXT) (samples: contributor, pm, architect)
  • allocation_percent (INTEGER) (samples: 29, 23, 95)
Relationships:
  • proj_id → projects.proj_id
  • emp_id → employees.emp_id

TABLE: assets
Rows: 2,000
Columns:
  • asset_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • name (TEXT) (samples: Laptop Air, Laptop Ground, Furniture Simple)
  • type (TEXT) (samples: Furniture, Transport, IT)
  • owner_emp (INTEGER) [FK → employees.emp_id] (samples: 4411, 8111, 3370)
  • purchase_date (TEXT) (samples: 2021-01-02, 2025-07-02, 2020-03-18)
  • value (REAL) (samples: 35375.0, 2918.09, 38569.51)
  • metadata_json (TEXT) (samples: {"warranty_years": 2, {"warranty_years": 4, {"warranty_years": 2)
Relationships:
  • owner_emp → employees.emp_id

TABLE: asset_history
Rows: 5,901
Columns:
  • hist_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • asset_id (INTEGER) [FK → assets.asset_id] (samples: 1)
  • change_date (TEXT) (samples: 2025-01-17, 2021-11-21, 2024-09-04)
  • note (TEXT) (samples: Enter modern executi, Course over investme, Threat want dog lose)
Relationships:
  • asset_id → assets.asset_id

TABLE: addresses
Rows: 10,995
Columns:
  • addr_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • emp_id (INTEGER) [FK → employees.emp_id] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • line1 (TEXT) (samples: 6090 Bell Bridge Apt, 9866 Victoria Canyon, 20863 Patricia Port )
  • city (TEXT) (samples: Martinberg, Jillianview, Rogersmouth)
  • state (TEXT) (samples: OH, OR, CT)
  • postal_code (TEXT) (samples: 57304, 04862, 44649)
  • country (TEXT) (samples: Portugal, Bolivia, Uruguay)
  • geo (TEXT) (samples: 67.0211,175.271332, -29.872242,-140.9197, -74.798829,24.815327)
  • is_primary (INTEGER) (samples: 1)
Relationships:
  • emp_id → employees.emp_id

TABLE: events
Rows: 30,058
Columns:
  • event_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • emp_id (INTEGER) [FK → employees.emp_id] (samples: 1, 2)
  • event_time (TEXT) (samples: 2024-01-14T07:37:35., 2024-12-14T16:53:33., 2023-01-22T12:44:33.)
  • event_type (TEXT) (samples: policy_ack, promotion)
  • details_json (TEXT) (samples: {"ip": "199.224.186., {"ip": "208.82.37.33, {"ip": "31.94.204.55)
  • created_at (TEXT) (samples: 2025-08-09T17:03:36., 2025-08-09T17:03:36., 2025-08-09T17:03:36.)
Relationships:
  • emp_id → employees.emp_id

TABLE: salaries
Rows: 24,999
Columns:
  • sal_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY] (samples: 1, 2, 3)
  • emp_id (INTEGER) [FK → employees.emp_id] (samples: 1, 2)
  • effective_date (TEXT) (samples: 2024-10-07, 2025-03-25, 2022-03-13)
  • salary (REAL) (samples: 71287.43, 52508.66, 22119.79)
  • reason (TEXT) (samples: raise, correction, hire)
  • created_at (TEXT) (samples: 2025-08-09T17:03:37., 2025-08-09T17:03:37., 2025-08-09T17:03:37.)
Relationships:
  • emp_id → employees.emp_id

TABLE: audit_log
Rows: 0
Columns:
  • audit_id (INTEGER) [PRIMARY KEY]
  • table_name (TEXT)
  • action (TEXT)
  • row_id (TEXT)
  • diff (TEXT)
  • created_at (TEXT)
